choices.text:
by.....foot?

Nursery School Teachers here are up in arms because the pay is only 700-1000 euros a month.

Being up in arms about a job ofa person who is not an old people doesn't make much sense. Because we have enough of old people who used to make a lot more... that nobody really is stressed when their social security gets cut a bit. They all talk about what's not enough but it's good enough never the less.There are a lot of good teaching jobs out there. But I doubt you will find one where you wont have to take lesson planning and similar work home. But why would you want to work in planning lessons for other people outside of your working hours? Your free time is your own. Take it, enjoy it.Now if the person doesn't have any qualifications and is trying to teach with a degree in something else from another country but should have been able to teach by the qualifications... that is a different story. Because knowing why you're there in another country and play the game... that is your own choice. It's not like you walked in one day and started working because it was the only job available(why a nursery school teacher would go to Estonia?). My brother is a music professor and in Poland they dont give a shit about his teaching... and they pass people on anything. But we complain because no one listens to good music over there... in same cases it pays to be a prostitute or drug cartel member.Ain
